Privacy Policy for HomeTalk Google Assistant Integration
Effective Date: July 22, 2024

1. Introduction
Welcome to HomeTalk. Your privacy is very important to us, and this Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use the HomeTalk Google Assistant Integration.

2. Information We Collect
We collect the following types of information to provide and improve our services:

User Authentication Information: We use Firebase Authentication to verify your identity when you link your HomeTalk account to Google Assistant. This includes your email address and any other authentication credentials you provide.
Device Information: We access information about your HomeTalk smart devices (such as device names, types, and statuses) to enable voice control via Google Assistant.
Usage Data: We collect data about how you interact with the HomeTalk Google Assistant Integration, such as the commands you use and the responses from your devices.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your information in the following ways:

To Provide Services: Your information is used to connect and control your HomeTalk devices through Google Assistant. This allows you to turn devices on/off, adjust settings, and check statuses using voice commands.
To Improve Services: We analyze usage data to enhance the functionality and performance of the HomeTalk Google Assistant Integration. This helps us understand how users interact with our services and identify areas for improvement.
To Ensure Security: We use your information to maintain the security of our services and protect against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction of data.
4. Information Sharing
We do not share your personal information with third parties, except in the following circumstances:

Service Providers: We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in delivering the Google Assistant functionality. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and use it only for the purposes of providing the service.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).
Protection of Rights: We may disclose your information to protect our rights, property, or safety, as well as the rights, property, or safety of our users or others.
5. Security
We take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include encryption, access controls, and secure data storage practices.

6. Your Rights
You have the following rights regarding your personal information:

Access: You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you.
Correction: You have the right to request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete personal information we hold about you.
Deletion: You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain exceptions (e.g., where we are required to retain the information by law).
